Veropharm Climbs Second Day on 21% First-Half Profit Gain

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-09-14T15:39:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/veropharm-climbs-for-second-day-on-21-percent-jump-in-profit.html
OAO  Veropharm (VRPH)  climbed for the
second day after the Russian pharmaceuticals company said net
profit for the first half of this year jumped 21 percent to 881
million rubles ($29 million) from 729 million rubles a year ago.  Its stock advanced as much as 4.1 percent before closing
1.7 percent higher at 961.9 rubles at 6:45 p.m. in Moscow.  Revenue rose 18 percent to 3.15 billion rubles, according
to an e-mailed statement from the company today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  